      "name": "T-34/76 (1942)",
      "desc": "The tank that saved the Soviet Union. Sloped armour that bounced shells the German 37mm couldn't penetrate, wide tracks that floated over mud and snow, and a 76mm gun that killed anything the Wehrmacht fielded in 1941. She was crude, cramped, and produced in numbers that defied belief.",
      "notes": "The T-34 is the Eastern Front's defining vehicle. She's individually outmatched by late-war German armour but she never fights alone. Use her in waves \u2014 the first T-34 the players destroy is a relief, the fifth is routine, the fifteenth is a nightmare. Numbers are the Soviet doctrine and the T-34 is the instrument.",
