      "name": "KV-1",
      "desc": "The heavy tank that terrified the Wehrmacht in 1941. Her armour was so thick that German anti-tank guns bounced off at point-blank range. At Raseiniai, a single KV-1 held up an entire German division for a day. She was slow, unreliable, and for a brief window absolutely invincible.",
